EXAMPLE RESOURCES

Space For Change Challenge Video
https://youtu.be/mrqzdXQzdeE?list=PL37Yhb2zout05pUjr7OoRFpTNroq_wd9f

Environmental Justice: A Call to Action with NASA Earth Observations
Learn more about examples of environmental injustices around the world and how NASA data can be applied to address these issues.
https://appliedsciences.nasa.gov/our-impact/story/environmental-justice-call-action-nasa-earth-observations

NASA Resources for Learning and Talking about Racism and Inequality
https://www.nasa.gov/centers/hq/eodm/documents_resources/resources_for_learning_and_talking_about_racism_and_inequality

NASA Data Pathfinders
NASA Data Pathfinders can help guide you in identifying appropriate data products for specific topics e.g. related to health and air quality, sea level change.
https://earthdata.nasa.gov/learn/pathfinders

NASA Socioeconomic Data and Applications Center (SEDAC)
NASA Socioeconomic Data and Applications Center (SEDAC) shares resources that support the integration of socioeconomic and Earth science data.
https://sedac.ciesin.columbia.edu/

United Nations Environment Programme Science Data
United Nations Environment Programme Science Data site shares data relevant to environmental rights and governance.
https://www.unep.org/science-data

United Nations Statistics Division Environment Statistics
https://unstats.un.org/unsd/envstats/climatechange.cshtml

EPA Environmental Justice Screening and Mapping Tool
EPA Environmental Justice Screening and Mapping Tool combines environmental and demographic indicators in maps and reports.
https://www.epa.gov/ejscreen

NASA's Black Marble resources
NASA's Black Marble resources shares remotely sensed lights at night data to better understand human-environment interactions.
https://blackmarble.gsfc.nasa.gov/

US Department of Health and Human Services GeoHEALTH Platform
https://geohealth.hhs.gov/arcgis/home/

US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention’s Health Equity website
https://www.cdc.gov/healthequity/index.html

US Census Bureau’s COVID-19 Site with demographic and economic resources.
https://covid19.census.gov/

NASA’s Software Catalog
NASA’s Software Catalog offers software programs, including environmental science programs, ready for download at no cost.
NASA’s Software Catalog is a product of NASA’s Technology Transfer Program.
https://software.nasa.gov/

NASA Technology Transfer
NASA Technology Transfer program ensures technologies developed by and for NASA are broadly available to the public (only items public domain technologies and resources can be applied to your Space Apps solution).
https://technology.nasa.gov/

NASA Spinoff
NASA Spinoff highlights examples of NASA technologies and how their applications have benefited life on Earth.
https://spinoff.nasa.gov/

SDGs Data Hub
Data hub to advance the production and use of real-time and geo-referenced data for Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs).
https://sdgstoday.org/
